-- Defending Champion Italy Trails 1-0 to Paraguay at Halftime in World Cup
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-14T19:17:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/defending-champion-italy-trails-1-0-to-paraguay-at-halftime-in-world-cup.html

          
          
             Antolin Alcaraz gave Paraguay a 1-0
halftime lead against defending champion Italy in the opening
match of Group F at soccer’s World Cup in Cape Town, South
Africa.   
 Alcaraz outjumped Fabio Cannavaro to head past goalkeeper
Gianluigi Buffon after 39 minutes.  
 Italy, which has progressed from the group stage at the
past eight World Cups, is aiming to match Brazil’s record five
titles.  
 New Zealand and Slovakia are also in Group F.  
          
          


  


        